            <li><strong>Diwali:</strong> The festival of lights celebrated with enthusiasm and fervor.</li>
            <p>Diwali, the Festival of Lights, is celebrated with great enthusiasm in Mumbai, transforming the city into a dazzling spectacle. Streets and homes are adorned with colorful lights, intricate rangoli designs, and decorative diyas, while fireworks fill the night sky with excitement. Families perform rituals dedicated to Lakshmi, the goddess of wealth, offering prayers and sweets in hopes of prosperity for the year ahead. Local markets buzz with energy as residents shop for new clothes, gifts, and festive treats, embodying the spirit of abundance and renewal.</p>
            <p>
                The sense of community is especially strong during Diwali, with neighbors and friends gathering to share sweets and celebrate. Cultural performances and traditional music resonate throughout the city, while children engage in activities like bursting crackers and creating colorful rangoli, adding to the overall merriment. This collective joy reinforces social bonds, making the festival a truly shared experience.
            </p>
            <p>
                Iconic landmarks such as the Gateway of India and Marine Drive are beautifully illuminated, enhancing the grandeur of the celebrations. The vibrant tapestry of lights and sounds reflects Mumbai’s rich traditions and communal harmony. Beyond being a celebration of wealth and prosperity, Diwali serves as a time for reflection and gratitude, encapsulating the spirit of Mumbai—a city thriving on its diversity and unity.
            </p>
