            <li><strong>Gudi Padwa:</strong> A significant festival for the Muslim community, celebrated with prayers and feasting.</li>
            <p>Gudi Padwa marks the Marathi New Year and is celebrated with great enthusiasm in Mumbai. Festivities begin with the hoisting of the "Gudi," a decorated pole adorned with a bright cloth, flowers, and a sugar garland, symbolizing prosperity and good fortune. People clean and decorate their homes, creating beautiful rangoli designs at the entrance. Traditional dishes like puran poli and shrikhand are prepared and shared with family and friends. The day is filled with cultural activities, including dance, music, and processions. Mumbai's streets come alive with festive spirit, as locals don new clothes and visit temples to seek blessings for the year ahead. Overall, Gudi Padwa is a vibrant celebration of renewal and community.</p>

